## Day 2 — Modern UI Styling with CSS Modules & Tailwind

🟢 **Beginner:** Styling decides how your app *looks*. **CSS Modules** scope styles to one component so they never leak elsewhere. **Tailwind CSS** is a "utility-first" approach: instead of writing CSS, you add tiny classes directly in your markup (`className="flex gap-4 p-6 rounded-xl"`).

🔵 **Advanced:** CSS Modules generate unique class names at build time (`Card_title__a1b2c`), eliminating global-namespace collisions — great for component isolation. Tailwind trades that for *speed and consistency*: a design-token system (spacing, color, type scale) enforced through classes, with the unused CSS purged at build for tiny bundles. Learn responsive prefixes (`md:`, `lg:`), state variants (`hover:`, `focus:`), and Flexbox/Grid utilities. Know when each shines: Tailwind for rapid, consistent product UI; CSS Modules for complex bespoke components. You'll use Tailwind to make Zero Hunger responsive across phone and desktop.

