## Day 3 — Docker Basics (Containerization), Run MERN in a Container, Deployment (AWS / Vercel / Render / Netlify)

🟢 **Beginner:** **Docker** packages your app *and everything it needs* into a **container** that runs the same on any machine — "it works on my laptop" becomes "it works everywhere." Then you **deploy** it to a hosting platform so the public can use it.

🔵 **Advanced:** Write a **Dockerfile** per service (multi-stage builds to keep images small), use a `.dockerignore`, and orchestrate the full stack (frontend, backend, MongoDB) with **Docker Compose** via a single `docker-compose.yml` and a shared network. For deployment, a common split: host the **React frontend** on Vercel/Netlify (static + CDN), the **Node/Express API** on Render/Railway/AWS, and the database on **MongoDB Atlas**. Configure environment variables and CORS for the production domain, and connect your GitHub Actions pipeline so a merge to `main` deploys automatically. Add basic **logging and monitoring** for health.

📖 **Read:**
- [Docker — Get started / Docker 101](https://docs.docker.com/get-started/)
